Sierra Leone Inflation Accelerates to 17.8% in May on Fuel, Food Costs

-- B y   S i l a s   G b a n d i a
-- 
2011-07-06T10:49:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-06/sierra-leone-inflation-accelerates-to-17-8-in-may-on-fuel-food-costs.html
Inflation in  Sierra Leone  accelerated
to 17.8 percent in May from 15.4 percent a month earlier,
according to Statistics Sierra Leone.  The increase in the rate was led by higher prices for fuel
and food, the agency said in the statement handed to reporters
in Freetown, the capital, today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
